{
  "text": "There are three forces at play in our model: [CITATION_1] Higher variety leads to increased market demand; [CITATION_2] This also leads to a higher relative demand variability for each product; (3) At the same time, the demand aggregation effect for the common components mitigates the increased costs associated with higher demand variability. In view of these three effects, we investigate how the choice of an assembly configuration (or bill of materials) affects a firm's assortment and stocking decisions.",
  "correct_citation": {
